# Double Diamond 常見誤用 將兩個鑽石套用在不同問題層級 是否合理：雙鑽石 Double Diamond 官方定義 經典用法 vs 個人問題到商業化兩階段套用

## 來源列表
1. [The Double Diamond — Design Council](https://www.designcouncil.org.uk/resources/the-double-diamond/) — n.d. / accessed 2026-05-10
2. [What is the double diamond model? — Dovetail](https://dovetail.com/design-thinking/double-diamond-model/) — 2026-04-15
3. [The Double Diamond Design Process — Splunk](https://www.splunk.com/en_us/blog/learn/double-diamond-design-process.html) — 2024-06-14
4. [Double Diamond Is Not How Most Companies Work — Smart Interface Design Patterns](https://smart-interface-design-patterns.com/articles/double-diamond-process/) — 2023-10-15
5. [Using the MPPF Method in the Double Diamond Design Process — Designorate](https://www.designorate.com/using-the-mppf-method-in-the-double-diamond-design-process/) — 2024-04-22 / updated 2024-04-27
6. [Multiple perspective problem framing in the design of self-administered treatments — ResearchGate / Design for Health](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/396921022_Multiple_perspective_problem_framing_in_the_design_of_self-administered_treatments) — 2025-10
7. [Competition brief: design foundations 2017 round 1 — GOV.UK](https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/funding-competition-design-foundations-2017-round-1/competition-brief-design-foundations-2017-round-1) — updated 2017-02-15, withdrawn 2017-09-21
8. [Problem Framing Expertise in Public and Social Innovation — ScienceDirect](https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2405872618301114) — Spring 2019

## 原文摘錄
### 來源 1
> The first diamond helps people understand, rather than simply assume, what the problem is.

### 來源 2
> Each diamond represents a cycle of divergent thinking—expanding outward to explore possibilities—followed by convergent thinking—narrowing inward to reach a decision.

### 來源 3
> Projects don’t always start from Phase 1.

### 來源 4
> Double Diamond works in theory, but not in practice.

### 來源 5
> problem definition keeps changing as we build more and more understanding of it

### 來源 6
> The former two stages focus on defining the problem that needs to be solved

### 來源 7
> ongoing development of ideas towards commercialisation and next steps in the innovation process

### 來源 8
> The evolutionary patterns of framing in public and social innovation are non-linear.

## 關鍵重點
- 官方定義把第一個鑽石放在「理解／定義問題」，第二個鑽石放在「發展／交付解法」；不是明確說兩個鑽石可分別套到不同層級的問題。（對應來源 1、2、6）
- 近期實務文章反覆指出常見誤用是把 Double Diamond 當線性流程、從 Phase 1 開始、每案完整走完；實務上可能中途開始、回到前面階段、或反覆迭代。（對應來源 2、3、4、5、8）
- 商業化相關來源有把 Double Diamond 放在 early-stage design / innovation journey / commercialisation 前段使用，但不是把「個人問題」與「商業化」明確定義成兩個不同鑽石。（對應來源 7）
- 關於「將兩個鑽石套用在不同問題層級是否合理」，找到的資料多支持「可彈性改編、問題定義會演化、問題／解法空間可來回移動」；但沒有找到代表性來源直接說「第一鑽石處理個人問題，第二鑽石處理商業化問題」這種套法是標準用法。（對應來源 2、5、6、8）

## 不確定點
- 無資料：沒有找到官方或代表性資料直接討論「把兩個鑽石分別套用在不同問題層級」這個命題。
- 無資料：沒有找到直接支持「個人問題到商業化」可被視為 Double Diamond 兩個鑽石的標準解釋。
- 可查到的相近說法是：Double Diamond 可用於 innovation / business model / commercialisation 前段，但來源仍把四階段維持在 discover、define、develop、deliver 的問題空間與解法空間邏輯內。
